<h1>LG Washer dE Error Code — Fix It Same Day</h1>

<p>dE on an LG washer means it can't confirm the door is locked, so it refuses to start the cycle — water can't run until the machine knows the door is sealed shut. Often it's just laundry caught in the seal or a door not pushed fully closed; when it's not, the door lock assembly has usually failed. Here's how to tell the difference. Same-day across LA, Orange County and Ventura. Call (323) 990-7550.</p>

<h2>What the dE Code Means</h2>
<p>dE is a door-lock fault. An LG washer won't let water in or start a cycle until the door (or lid) latch confirms it's locked shut — it's a safety interlock. dE means that confirmation never arrived: the control told the lock to engage and didn't get the signal back that it did. On some models you'll see it as dE1 or dE2, which are the same door-lock family. Until the machine sees a locked door, it simply won't run.</p>

<h2>What Causes a dE Error on an LG Washer</h2>
<p>In order of how often we find it:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>A door not pushed fully shut</strong> — it needs a firm close until it clicks.</li>
  <li><strong>Laundry or the rubber seal edge caught in the latch area</strong>, blocking the door from seating.</li>
  <li><strong>A worn or broken door lock assembly</strong> — the latch and its switch.</li>
  <li><strong>A loose connector or damaged wiring</strong> at the lock.</li>
  <li><strong>A control-board fault</strong> — rare.</li>
</ul>

<h2>What You Can Safely Check Yourself First</h2>
<p>Open the door and look at the rubber seal and the latch — make sure no laundry is pinched in the way and the strike isn't blocked. Wipe the latch and the catch it seats into so nothing's holding it open. Then push the door firmly shut until you hear it click. Power-cycle the washer (off for a minute, back on) and start a cycle. If it locks and dE clears, you've got it.</p>

<h2>When It's the Door Lock Assembly (and What We Do)</h2>
<p>If nothing's caught and the door still won't confirm locked, the door lock assembly itself has usually worn out — it's the most common part we replace for dE. The latch holds the door and a switch inside tells the control it's secured; when that switch stops closing reliably, you get dE on a door that looks shut. Our techs test the latch continuity and the switch directly, then fit a new assembly. Door lock assembly replacement runs $250–320 installed. The $65 diagnostic is waived when we do the repair.</p>

<h2>dE vs Other LG Codes</h2>
<p>dE is strictly about the door and lock — the cycle won't even begin. IE means it started but won't fill with water; OE means it filled and washed but won't drain. If your washer is starting and running before it faults, you're looking at IE or OE, not dE.</p>

